threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, 32-bit

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary exhibits multiple high-confidence indicators of malicious obfuscation and shellcode-like behavior. Key indicators include a writable and executable .text section, the total absence of an Import Table (suggesting dynamic API resolution via PEB traversal), and several functions containing XOR-based decryption loops (e.g., sub_401194, sub_40118b) typical of malware packers or stagers. The entry point and associated subroutines use anti-analysis techniques such as opaque predicates and manual stack manipulation to hinder decompilation and static analysis.
